Mobile phone service provider Airtel Networks Kenya Limited has moved its mobile cash transfer service to Airtel Money Kenya Limited. The telco said this is for purpose of rendering better services to its customers. "Following this business separation, Airtel Money Kenya Limited will take over and continue the provision of Airtel Money Services in collaboration with licensed telecommunications network of Airtel Networks Kenya Limited," Airtel Networks said in a statement Thursday. The transfer takes effect from Thursday, July 21, 2022. "The continued use of the Airtel Money Service shall be deemed as proof of customer's acceptance of the transfer of their Airtel Money Account and related customer data and or sharing of customer data between Airtel Money Kenya Limited and Airtel Networks Kenya Limited," the statement added.